text: Corfu is an unincorporated community in Grant County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Corfu was established in 1910, and remained in operation until 1943. The community was named after the island of Corfu, in Greece. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Grant County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Corfu, Washington
